<br>
The soldiers of Iraq are dragging women and children out as human shields against the coallition. They are slaughtering citizens that cheer at what they think is their liberation. They are dressing as American and British soldiers, and going into homes and slaughtering people. All of this has been proven by fact in the recent days (even the press, who is by no means in favor of the military actions has admitted this), and still I read stupid people bitching about foreign policy leaders, and having no right to be there.<br>
<br>
Since when did this world get so damn self centered?! Nobody stood for this when Hitler was doing this to the Jews. Yet, it is ok for Saddam to do that to the unimportant Iraqi people. Who gives a shit about them?! Man, we have some F'ed up leaders to want to go in there and take this guy out. He should be left to his own schemes. He should be allowed to slaughter his own women and children as he wishes. Shit, they are only Iraqis right?! Hell, we Canadians, Americans, French, German, and whatever else have bigger things to be concerned with. Like dolphins being caught in nets, and taxes and such!<br>
<br>
Heartless bastards. Makes me ashamed to be a part of the human race at times. Who gives a RATS ASS about who started what. The bastages are slaughtering their own people in order to be victorious. And all we can do is bitch about ourselves and about how important our opinions are. <br>
<br>
Everyone stop and look at your own loved ones, and imagine you lived over there under that regime. And imagine the whole world crying about how unimportant your freedom is. How nobody should be going in and liberating you. How nothing is WRONG! Yet that night, your wife/sister/daughter/mother is dragged out into the street. Tied to a cross post, in the forward leaning position. And has her tongue cut off in public, left there leaning forward to bleed to death. This happened because she said &quot;she hopes the American, and British forces free them soon. And that Saddam does not care about their safety.&quot;<br>
That is not a fictional story. I have seen the pictures of this. It is very mind numbing and terrifying. Al Jezeera celebrated this like it was a great event. She was left in town square for 2 days as a warning to those that speek against Saddam.<br>
<br>
So next time you want to post about &quot;Foriegn Policy Leaders&quot;, or &quot;They have no right to be there&quot;, you think about what those people live under. Do they not trust the American/British forces? Nope, they dont. Because 12 years ago, we promised them freedom, and they rose up. And then we left them without that freedom, and they suffered for it. Now we have to prove to them that we are there for their freedom, and that we WILL win.<br>
<br>
Opinions matter, but for the sake of all that is decent, think about those that are TRULY suffering. Not about your own whims and wants. Hell, I wish we were not there. I think we should be dealing with domestic problems at home in America, not being the world police. Not sending units all over every time someone screams help. But then I stop and think about those people that need the help. Who else is going to do it? Who else will jump up and offer their lives for someone they dont know? Right now, only the Coallition party will. <br>
<br>
Want to talk about money? Talk about being in it for oil or whatever? Hell, the coallition party will be lucky to not go bankrupt when this thing is over. Even if they siezed all the current oil in Iraq, it would barely cover costs of the war, not alone rebuilding. Again, I dont see anyone else jumping in to help rebuild for the Iraqi people when it is done.<br>
<br>
<br>
Khelendrose Frostweaver<br>
